SENATE RESOLUTION 356
By Akbari
A RESOLUTION to celebrate the tenth anniversary of the
Vintage901 Wine, Food and Music Festival.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this legislative body should pause to honor
and congratulate those community events that are sources of great civic pride; and
WHEREAS, one such event is the Vintage901 Wine, Food and Music Festival, which will
celebrate its tenth anniversary this year; and
WHEREAS, the Vintage901 Wine, Food and Music Festival was organized in 2016 as a
heartfelt tribute to founder Stephanie Ferreira's spouse; Ms. Ferreira, along with four of her
friends, chose to establish a nonprofit organization to create both memorable experiences and
an enduring legacy of service and community; and
WHEREAS, since its inception, the Vintage901 Wine, Food and Music Festival has
evolved into a vibrant, mission-driven movement rooted in the spirit of Memphis; and
WHEREAS, for a decade, Vintage901 has continued to celebrate the rich intersection of
wine, food, music, and community, proudly serving as a cultural and philanthropic pillar of the
Memphis community; and
WHEREAS, in recent years, Vintage901 has further deepened its mission by focusing on
underserved students and providing scholarships to those pursuing studies and careers in
culinary arts, viticulture, viniculture, enology, and the wine business, cultivating the next
generation of talent while also expanding opportunities in these industries; and
WHEREAS, Vintage901 directly supports programs that strengthen and enrich the
community and has contributed more than $200,000 to local nonprofit organizations, including
the Women's Foundation, the National Civil Rights Museum, the Overton Park Shell, Hope
House, and the Memphis Symphony, among many other worthy organizations; and
SR0356
